meanings.definition: (方言, スコットランド) 陰嚢

etymology.value: Origin uncertain. Possibly related to Middle English *mockett* (“napkin, cloth”), from Old French *mouchet* (“spot, patch”).

usage_notes.explanation: This word is primarily used in Scotland and is considered dialectal. It is a vulgar term.

readability_explanation.text: This is a very rare and dialectal term, primarily used in Scotland. It is not part of standard English vocabulary.
